<br>
Also, intense heating of the plate from these fluxes affects your material choices. I am not referring to the thermal pulse from the a-bomb (which is dealt with via a thin ablation layer) but the penetrating radiation heating. Some material also undergo neutron activation. This may require active cooling - the design of which may effect materal choices.<br>
